{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:43:14.272048+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here is the complete breakdown of the predefined subcommands registered in `gita/cmds.json`:\n\n## Subcommands and Their Underlying `git` Commands\n\n| Subcommand | `git` Command | `allow_all` | `disable_async` | Help Text |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `br` | `git branch -vv` | – | – | show local branches |\n| `clean` | `git clean -dfx` | – | – | remove all untracked files/folders |\n| `diff` | `git diff` | – | – | git show differences |\n| `difftool` | `git difftool` | – | ✅ `true` | show differences using a tool |\n| `fetch` | `git fetch` | ✅ `true` | – | fetch remote update |\n| `last` | `git log -1 HEAD` | – | – | show log information of HEAD |\n| `lo` | `git log --oneline -7` | ✅ `true` | – | show one-line log for the latest 7 commits |\n| `log` | `git log` | – | ✅ `true` | show logs |\n| `merge` | `git merge @{u}` | – | – | merge remote updates |\n| `mergetool` | `git mergetool` | – | ✅ `true` | merge updates with a tool |\n| `patch` | `git format-patch HEAD~` | – | – | make a patch |\n| `pull` | `git pull` | ✅ `true` | – | pull remote updates |\n| `push` | `git push` | ✅ `true` | – | push the local updates |\n| `rebase` | `git rebase` | – | – | rebase from master |\n| `reflog` | `git reflog` | – | – | show ref logs |\n| `remote` | `git remote -v` | – | – | show remote settings |\n| `reset` | `git reset` | – | – | reset repo(s) |\n| `show` | `git show` | – | ✅ `true` | show detailed commit information |\n| `stash` | `git stash` | – | – | store uncommitted changes |\n| `stat` | `git diff --stat` | ✅ `true` | – | show edit statistics |\n| `st` | `git status` | ✅ `true` | – | show status |\n| `tag` | `git tag -n` | – | – | show tags |\n\n**Total: 22 subcommands**\n\n---\n\n### Entries with `allow_all: true` (6 entries)\n\nThese commands opt into `allow_all`, meaning they can operate across **all** managed repos simultaneously rather than requiring a specific repo to be selected:\n\n1. **`fetch`** → `git fetch`\n2. **`lo`** → `git log --oneline -7`\n3. **`pull`** → `git pull`\n4. **`push`** → `git push`\n5. **`stat`** → `git diff --stat`\n6. **`st`** → `git status`\n\n---\n\n### Entries with `disable_async: true` (4 entries)\n\nThese commands opt out of asynchronous execution — they run sequentially/synchronously (likely because they are interactive or require terminal I/O):\n\n1. **`difftool`** → `git difftool`\n2. **`log`** → `git log`\n3. **`mergetool`** → `git mergetool`\n4. **`show`** → `git show`\n\n---\n\n### No entries have **both** `allow_all` and `disable_async` set simultaneously. The two flags are used on entirely disjoint sets of commands.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 835, "prompt_tokens": 7387, "total_tokens": 8222, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 17, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 5952}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "8fcb6348c03240a1acae1440dcd38f83", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead7a-ea7d-7860-84bf-cfcec59649b3-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7387, "output_tokens": 835, "total_tokens": 8222, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 5952}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 17}}}}]}}}
